  "texts": [
    "We think that it is not implausible to consider Jamal a co-creator, albeit a distant one.",
    "Nevertheless, even a weaker claim to co-creatorship may ground derivative claims, e.g., to be appropriately credited or asked for consent.",
    "Reasonably, Jamal may decline to be a co-creator on prompting endeavors by people he does not know and whose values he may not share (see e.g.",
    "Importantly, CCC makes clear that he may do so on grounds that are independent from concerns about intellectual property violations in scraping and using imagery for training GenAI.",
    "In virtue of this, CCC also reinforces arguments pushing back against awarding users exclusive copyright over GenAI outputs, especially if they do not exert sufficient effort and control, and others, like Jamal, may have co-creatorship claims [28].CCC also generates novel intuitions, for example, that GenAI systems have the capacity to create illusions of creatorship."
